
1️⃣ Start Your Spring Boot Server

Run the application.

You should see:

Tomcat started on port 8765

So your base URL is:

http://localhost:8765
2️⃣ Login to Get JWT Token
Request

POST

http://localhost:8765/auth/login
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "username": "TT0001",
  "password": "pass"
}
Expected Response
{
  "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9....",
  "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...."
}

Copy the accessToken.

3️⃣ Store Token in Postman (Optional but Recommended)

In Tests tab of login request:

pm.environment.set("token", pm.response.json().accessToken);

Now Postman automatically stores the token.

4️⃣ Add Employee (Authorized Request)
Request

POST
http://localhost:8765/employee

Headers
Authorization: Bearer token: token
Content-Type: application/json

Body
{
  "name": "Rohit Kumar",
  "companyEmail": "rohit.kumar@techwave.com",
  "personalEmail": "rohitkumar@gmail.com",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
  "address": "Hyderabad",
  "department": "IT",
  "designation": "Backend Developer",
  "dateOfJoin": "2024-01-01",
  "dateOfBirth": "1996-05-20",
  "description": "Spring Boot developer",
  "roles": ["EMPLOYEE"]
}

5️⃣ Expected Response
{
  "empId": "TT0002",
  "name": "Rohit Kumar",
  "companyMail": "rohit.kumar@techwave.com",
  "department": "IT",
  "personalMail": "rohitkumar@gmail.com",
  "address": "Hyderabad",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
  "designation": "Backend Developer",
  "dateOfJoin": "2024-01-01"
}

6️⃣ Flow Diagram
POST /auth/login
        │
        ▼
Verify username/password
        │
        ▼
Generate JWT token
        │
        ▼
Use token in Authorization header
        │
        ▼
POST /employee
        │
        ▼
JwtAuthenticationFilter validates token
        │
        ▼
Controller executes
        │
        ▼
Employee created